Block is the main class - it's what we make here at the Block Factory. In the DB, it is its own document. We sell standard BlockModels. There are numerous Blocks, plus Instructions, in a BlockModel. (We also build CustomBlockModels at the request of Clients.
In a BlockModel, we refer the Blocks it contains using the class BlockModelPart. It contains an attribute blockSummary that contains a summary of the data of a Block. It presents it in an abbreviated and denormalized form. That's what the hint above means.
